The paper deals with the expressive power of unambiguous automata on infinite trees, which is a topic in formal language theory and automata theory. The paper also introduces and uses the notion of the (parity or Rabin-Mostowski) index hierarchy, which is a concept in logic and complexity theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also involves the study of regular tree languages, which falls under the sub-category cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper uses the theory of signatures in parity games, which is a topic in algorithmic game theory and falls under the sub-category cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also involves the study of alternating parity tree automata, which is a topic in computational complexity and falls under the sub-category cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper constructs canonical signatures, which is a topic in programming languages and falls under the sub-category cs.PL (Programming Languages).
